D.q[6195] = "";
D.q[7726] = "";
D.q[292] = "It\'s a revolutionary idea but it needs lots of testing. I\'m actually using Chafer Archer Thighbone, ground into a powder, to simulate the taste of curry. The right mix is really difficult to find, plus, I\'m running out of thighbones.";
D.q[7739] = "Well, we\'re not lacking for bodies, but the men are tired and wild beasts roam the forest. We also have to constantly fight against the port freezing over and we\'re running out of fuel for our boilers. It would be great if you could fetch me 10 Aspen Wood.";
D.q[5080] = "";
D.q[7697] = "Ahh, it\'s nice to see a new face! Hello hello, I\'m Captain Ardier, master of the Sanguine, the magnificent ship you can see behind me. Isn\'t she beautiful? This proud galleon broke the ice around Frigost, braved the waves of the Antinau Sea and landed here in Amakna. Impressed? Of course you are, but the most surprising thing is that she is ready to set sail again and head due north to the port of Frigost. I bet you don\'t know anything about Frigost, do you? Why don\'t you come along too? You look like the adventurous sort, and throughout the journey, I\'ll regale you with tales of this magical island, dangerous like a jealous woman and a full of unparalleled wealth.";
D.q[3686] = "All clear. Secured Area.";
D.q[7740] = "You must have Frigostian blood in your veins, that\'s the only explanation for your strength! I\'ll ask the lads to dry the wood. If you\'ve got any more, I\'ll happily take it.";
D.q[3447] = "The Filtounga is a recipe a bit heavy, but it\'s delicious! DEEE-LISH-ISSSS!!!";
D.q[6437] = "Hello! My name is Cheeka and I\'m the leader of an important group of merchants. When I\'m not doing business, I\'m doing businessmen and believe me, I know exactly how to mix business with pleasure! They say I\'m very stiff when it comes to business, but believe me - they\'re the ones who are stiff! So what do you think about it?";
D.q[7701] = "There you go, everything went smoothly. You\'re finally on Frigost, well, in its port, anyway. If you\'re a little lost, don\'t hesitate to talk to Haka, he knows a lot of people and will show you around.";
D.q[7699] = "Ah, there you are matey! Let me tell you a little about the inhabitants of the island. They are strong and courageous. Despite the cold weather that prevails, they have all managed to adapt and overcome the challenge. We are also ingenious, our homes are warm thanks to our pipeline system and steam. We have adapted, you see. You will notice pretty quickly that the creatures have also acclimatised. You\'ll see, you\'ll be warmly welcomed by all Frigost\'s citizens. If there\'s one person you should watch out for, however, it\'s the Count and his clique. They\'re an evil bunch who betrayed the Frigostians. Who is the Count? Oh, don\'t worry, I\'ll tell you everything about him.";
D.q[7702] = "Well, well, how are you? Isn\'t it a glorious day?";
D.q[7700] = "If you want to hear the truth about Frigost and Count Harebourg, you\'ve come to the right place. I know the truth, and despite what some people say, it\'s the whole truth! You see, a long time ago, we all worked for the Count. We were blinded by his unrealistic promises. Then his thirst for power went to his head. How could one man have such pretentions? Wanting to be the equal of a god - such arrogance! His acts could not remain unpunished and the island suffered Djaul\'s wrath. The Count, that traitor, remains sequestered in his castle and woe betide anyone who dares challenge him. But I think if one day a hero manages to defeat him, Djaul will grant us forgiveness. Maybe you\'re the one we\'re waiting for?";
D.q[3690] = "All clear, this area\'s safe and sound.";
D.q[7741] = "Thanks to the big freeze, I have been able to maintain a hundred percent organic farming technique. My calves are raised on grain and their fur is treated with products made from completely biodegradable plant matter. They\'re starving and eat what they can, fair enough, but they can survive now even if, unlike before, they don\'t have much to put in their mouths.\nThe only big problem is ticks. And don\'t talk to me about Frigostian ethics: they have no more than I do.";
D.q[1167] = "Hello! To come see me in this modest residence surrounded by stones and boulders, you must have the fisherman\'s fever too! \nOr you just want to talk to me about love and other nonsense.";
D.q[3342] = "Hello! Welcome on the Test Server!\n\nHere is a list of some of the novelties brought up by this BETA 1 Version 1.17.0:\n\n- Treechnid and Soft Oak Dungeons;\r\n            \n- Smithmagic system revised;\r\n            \n- Emoticons with the /me command;\r\n            \n- Blocking square problem has been fixed;\r\n            \n- A new automatic server selection system;\r\n            \n- A more detailed list of your character\'s characteristics.\n\nThis list isn\'t exhaustive. You can find a more detailed one on the forum in the Test Server section. On the top right-hand corner of your screen, next to the options menu, you\'ll now find a small button which will enable you to submit a problem you come across to the technical support. You can also talk about it on the forum.\n\nThere.... so, what can I do for you?";
D.q[7698] = "You see, the crossing isn\'t too bad, is it? We\'re lucky to have such a clear sky. If it continues like this, our journey will be a short one and we\'ll get to Frigost early. By Alma, it\'s good to talk to new friends! Tell me matey, do you know much about our beloved island, Frigost? Let me tell you about the delights it contains. Frigost is an island covered with ice and snow. But it wasn\'t always so. Long ago there were green pastures, golden shores and proud, pristine snow-capped mountains, ah, t\'was a sight to behold! A more beautiful land you will never hope to set foot on. But man\'s folly and the treachery of Count Harebourg condemned our beautiful island. But you see, our island is still beautiful. Who can boast of fields of pure white? Or a lake of pure, frozen water, that you can walk across? I see that I have awakened your curiosity. Come see me later and I\'ll tell you what I know about the inhabitants.";
D.q[6458] = "What do you want. There\'s no law against having a walk, is there? Leave me be!";
D.q[4975] = "What do you want! You\'re interrupting me in the middle of my research.";
D.q[6585] = "Sorry, I thought you were someone else, nobody followed you, did they? You should be more careful, you never know what\'s hiding in the shadows. \nBy the look of you I\'d say you had a few problems on the way here. Norb told you about the shortcut I hope?! \nWell if there\'s nothing else, I\'ve to get back to work.";
D.q[441] = "Hello, I\'m Hagal, the bank keeper. Only respectable persons who are not outlaws can enter.";
D.q[174] = "Ssssssshhhhh....Get losssssst, little maggot tail.... Only the vilessst beingssss in Amakna can vissssssssit our Massssssster, Vil Smisssse....\nSssshhhhhhh....Asssshhhhhh....Uuuuuusssshhh";
D.q[1354] = "*Paper*\nOh! I lost. You\'re not too bad... Round three!";
D.q[3693] = "Be careful, creatures round here can get aggressive.";
D.q[81] = "Hello, I\'ve a feeling that you\'d like to know more about my story...";
D.q[2140] = "What do you want? I don\'t have time to discuss the weather, leave me alone...";
D.q[1360] = "*Scissors*\nHem, but how ? It\'s not possible... Cheater!";
D.q[5321] = "";
D.q[5167] = "Hello, I was starting to believe that you\'d never come back. Have you found a Xelor who can cast a spell on this book to reveal its story?";
D.q[6745] = "Hello, I\'m a simple merchant. I only do business between Bonta and Astrub.";
D.q[6039] = "Hello, I\'m in a bit of a hurry so keep it short please.";
D.q[5695] = "Hello, I\'m looking for my two brothers, Aigurraf and Tabach. They\'re not feeling the best at the moment, they\'re behaving like kids. I\'m afraid they\'ll get themselves into trouble.";
D.q[175] = "Ssssshhhhhhh...our clansshhhh forcesssshhh usssshhh...Ssshhhh...to sssssssspeak like thhhisssssshhh..SSSSssssseeemssss it makessshhhh usssss look...Ssshhhh...even more evilssssshhhhh...";
D.q[3711] = "Piwiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiii";
D.q[3714] = "Hey! Watch out! I\'m carrying water to the nymphets. ";
D.q[347] = "To become jeweller, you first need to love jewellery, precious stones and rare metals. This profession requires lots of attention to detail and imagination. I can teach you the trade if you want, but you\'ll have to buy the right tool off me.\nJewellers use a Setter.";
D.q[6368] = "Shush, I said. Ask one question at a time, and keep your voice down.\nSo, rumours are rife of a magic horn in Sufokia and you want to know more about it? I haven\'t heard those rumours, I never leave this library. However, I do know the story of the horn, would you like to hear it?";
D.q[6638] = "No, they\'re white like the shell of a White Scaraleaf.";
D.q[6327] = "Hello, do you like animals too then?";
D.q[2556] = "So... vile Dofus hunter, world destroyer, chaotic tourist, do you have something to say for yourself?";
D.q[2460] = "Awesome! I\'m starting to understand how this plant mutation stuff works!\nI think till then we\'ll find the remedy... I don\'t know what\'ll happen if we don\'t.!";
D.q[349] = "I hate Moskitos, these unbearable little monsters always attack me for no reason when I\'m out cutting trees. \nIf you bring me 10 Moskito Wings, I\'ll give you a Lumberjack Axe.\nIf you bring me 100 of them all at once, I\'ll give you my Lumberjack Amulet.\n\nMoskitos are easy to find, above all near the Guilty Trees all around the lake.";
D.q[4778] = "I was just curious, there\'s no harm in that.";
D.q[364] = "Hi, I\'m Ness Laye. I\'m a confectioner of contentment, a harbinger of happiness... You guessed it, I\'m the only one who can make happiness flakes.";
D.q[405] = "There are mines almost everywhere on the mountainsides, but some are practically empty or infested with disreputable monsters. Walk alongside the mountain and you\'ll eventually find the entrances which lead to the different mines in the province of Amakna.";
D.q[4779] = "Well... I... you know... I wanted to catch him red-handed... you know?";
D.q[1123] = "Teeheehee HEH HEH HEH HEH!\nYou want to know why I\'m laughing? Give me 5 Kamas and I\'ll tell you...\nTeeheehee HEH HEH HEH HEH!";
D.q[4808] = "Hello, it\'s good to see you again. I hope the trial starts soon, it will shed more light on this alleged treason.";
D.q[4980] = "Hello, it\'s good to see you in such good spirits. The steward  would like to see you. I won\'t even bother telling you where he is, you must know by now.";
D.q[6549] = "Hello, is it you who fought the Brakmarians near Cania Bay?";
D.q[5215] = "";
D.q[3950] = "Hello, master Wabbit, can I help you? Would you like to check that everything\'s ready for the arrival of your prince?";
D.q[813] = "The Innkeeper at the Burnt Cat had his throat cut last night. Find out who the murderer is and give me their name!\nI\'d like to congratulate them and enlist them as an assassin, they\'ve done a great job!";
D.q[6009] = "Hello, my name is Professor Kalkulus.";
D.q[3740] = "A good lumberjack knows where to find the best trees in the forest of Amakna.";
D.q[1008] = "Here is a glittering necklace at last! You weren\'t very fast this time...";
D.q[360] = "Hello, my name is Lou, Lou Pachoups and I love lollipops. I learnt how to make them but I just don\'t have enough ingredients...";
D.q[5503] = "Hello, my name is Suebur Dirgah and I guard the keys. Nobody can climb these steps until they show me the key - pauper, soldier nor king.";
D.q[4783] = "The militia? Who do you take me for? I had no evidence and they would have dragged me off for defamation, the clowns! What do you think? They look after themselves.";
D.q[448] = "If you don\'t want to practise, you can always use scrolls. I collect Nimble Rings. Bring me a hundred or so of them and I\'ll give you a Little Parchment of Agility.";
D.q[1702] = "The Osamodas temple is located eastward of the village of Amakna. Talk to Lisa Modas to begin your training.";
D.q[7400] = "";
D.q[7159] = "";
D.q[4784] = "Well... I... you know... I wanted to catch him red-handed... you know?";
D.q[3745] = "Collecting resources is a simple and relatively quick way of earning your first few Kamas.";
D.q[2515] = "Hello, outsider! I must tell you that the sale of fermented products is strictly regulated on this island. These products must be taken in moderation. But our workshops are wide-open to you and your Kamas!";
D.q[5162] = "Hello, was your trip to the library worth the effort?";
D.q[1395] = "What do you want? We are in a danger zone. We could be attacked by these bloody Bontarians any minute! You\'d better leave.";
D.q[3750] = "Gutting a fish, is easy as pie. Use this fish workbench here, you\'ll see the result before you start. Don\'t forget that you must have your tool in your hand if you want to do anything related to your profession.";
D.q[4802] = "Congratulations on this excellent result.\nDanathor wants to talk to you, it seems urgent. While you\'re there I will ask Ture Inge to question the Sram.";
D.q[2357] = "What do you want?";
D.q[1061] = "What do you want?";
D.q[4853] = "";
D.q[1839] = "During my research for map making, I found a manuscript that indicates the positions of a few tunnels. One of them starts in the basement of the Library but I\'ve never been able to understand how the opening device works. I doubt someone like you\'ll be able to solve the puzzle!";
D.q[6090] = "What does it matter what others think, it\'s not as if they had accepted me as one of their own anyway.";
D.q[5617] = "What does this little Militiaman want with us? Go do this, go do that, wait here, meet me there. They say jump and he asks how high?. Pathetic.";
D.q[4689] = "Ah, you\'re back finally. Are you going to bring me what I need for the blade - the Corruptite. A very pretty name for a very rare material. It can only be found in the Blacksmith Dungeon, in the safe in the last room.";
D.q[7096] = "";
D.q[7160] = "";
D.q[3774] = "Do you wish to return to your statue, young one?";
D.q[2106] = "When I was in the Amakna cemetery one night for... well, don\'t worry about why I was there... Anyway, while I was walking through the cemetery, I heard voices coming from my grandfather\'s grave. They were saying Yke Harou...the attic...my Gobball...you\'ll find the Seer Blow!.Although I had been playing Goh for a while, I didn\'t know that legendary blow at the time, so I looked into it some research and I discovered the following passage - The One who will find the Seer Blow of the Goh game will be able to predict time and space. I know you\'ll just say I\'ve been sitting in this tavern for too long, but the following episode is even more exciting...";
D.q[2926] = "Hello, you culture vulture! So you\'ve come to get an education? Well, it\'s about time, and as we say, it\'s never too late to start... If you need a book, just ask me.";
D.q[318] = "Hello, we are the bankers. You can open an account here and you\'ll have a safe place in which to keep your property. Please note that each time you access your bank account, it will cost you #1 Kamas.";
D.q[3779] = "Do you wish to return to your statue, young one?";
D.q[3778] = "Do you wish to return to your statue, young one?";
D.q[6470] = "Hello, you look even more unhappy than I do! Why the long face?";
D.q[5326] = "";
D.q[433] = "Hello, young adventurer, I\'m one of the few breeders of Dreggons in this land... I\'ve been breeding and taming them for many years now... I\'m the only one who can truly understand and control them.\nBut I\'ve had some trouble in the last few years... maybe you could help me?";
D.q[696] = "Tears of joy blind my view,\nAnd this, adventurer, is thanks to you.\nKnowledge in your soul found bliss,\nHere is the expected secret, the Kiss...";
D.q[5407] = "";
D.q[7097] = "";
D.q[7161] = "";
D.q[4288] = "Hello. I\'m just about to have a rare rest, so I really don\'t want to talk.";
D.q[7098] = "";
D.q[4409] = "Excellent, perfect! That\'s exactly what we needed - a meeting at the Tower of Bonta. We\'ll be able to catch him there. Hmm, I guess we\'ll have to increase the guard around the perimeter though.";
D.q[1524] = "Excellent! You know how to fight now.... maybe you can be of some real help. I\'ll contact you if I need you. Until then, we\'ll have to be discreet.\nApparently you have a letter for me too... thanks. Next time try not to forget.";
D.q[7214] = "";
D.q[7464] = "";
D.q[5531] = "Hello. You are a fervent defender of Bonta, I am proud to meet you. My name is Jiva, I am proctetor of the month of Javian and of this splendid city.";
D.q[5170] = "Help me, please! I want to get out of here! The demon\'s frightening me... but these stupid Wabbits are even worse!";
D.q[2830] = "Today is meditation day. Don\'t disturb me!\n\n...ommmm.... ohm uh uh oh... ommmmm...";
D.q[130] = "Sometimes the Tavern organises feasts. Minstrels come and play to liven things up and the price of grilled Tofu generally drops by half. Meetings can also be organised here for the members of a guild or groups of friends.";
D.q[1027] = "Hem, form 243...You must have terrible doubts about someone if you need this test.";
D.q[576] = "Oh ho, you\'re serious! Alright, I\'ll help you. To be promoted, the Kanniball underlings have to fight between castes. The winner takes the loser\'s mask. When one has a mask of each of the four castes, he combines them to make a new mask. If you bring me the four masks, I\'ll combine them for you...";
D.q[7717] = "Listen matey, I\'m the head of the harbour, so show me some respect!\nI know that boats no longer leave since everything froze over, with some exceptions, but that doesn\'t mean that I\'m out of work!\nNo, I\'m not drinking... I\'m rinsing my throat while thinking, which is different altogether.\nWhat? You think I rinse my throat a lot? It\'s perfectly normal, it\'s to stop the inside of my throat freezing up because of the cold. Anyway, if I talk to much, it makes me thirsty. No, go get your own. If you\'re thirsty, go to the tavern.";
D.q[1550] = "Hem, I see clearly... Danathor\'s losing ground fast... this terrain doesn\'t suit him at all... hmmmpaoh... his rival Tedeor is coming through on the inside... the Bontarians are going wild... But what\'s this... oh my! A terrible accident, and Deanathor\'s not far behind, Tedeor\'s out of the race, what a shock result... and Danathor is crowned, yes, Danathor will be steward for some time to come.";
D.q[7761] = "Thank you, I hope you didn\'t pick the wrong Mastogob. \nWhile I examine them, go and fetch me some isotonic seawater but be careful, it must be as pure as possible. Cap\'n Tankerous is the only one who knows how to obtain it, so go and ask him.";
D.q[2766] = "A thousand and one rice grains opened up in the paddy-fields of our island since we last met. I know you feel ready to become a Danwa. Which level are you going to try to pass?";
D.q[592] = "Ah, finally, someone who understands! To fix the hole I need many pots of Glu and wood planks. If you bring me 2 planks and a pot of Glu, I\'ll give you a bottle of good rum. I\'ve got loads of the stuff!";
D.q[1443] = "Hem, you\'re looking for help with an interrogation?\nI suggest investigation form n°33, but that\'s 700 Kamas a copy...";
D.q[7162] = "";
D.q[7762] = "I\'ve almost none left, so hands off. If you want my isotonic sea water, you will have to give me something in return. I don\'t want any of that tourist tat, either, no, what I want is... Mugwort! It has completely disappeared from Frigost but I heard that Jon Burrowman still has some in stock. Bring some to me and I\'ll give you your water, and I don\'t care whether it\'s for fighting the Lurgi or for rinsing out your nose.";
D.q[5811] = "";
D.q[6107] = "Greeting. Have you any more information or secrets which could give us the upper hand against our enemy city?";
D.q[1438] = "Hem, you\'re looking for help with an interrogation?\nI suggest investigation form n°36, but it\'s 500 Kamas a copy...";
D.q[7763] = "Mugwort? Who told you that... Cap\'n Tankerous, right?\nThat drunkard laughed at me during the agricultural invention competition and you want me to forgive him just like that? Out of the question!\nHe can carry on carving ice cubes and drowning in his drink, that\'s all he deserves.";
D.q[5327] = "";
D.q[6108] = "A Brakmarian told me that the descendant of my cousin is locked into Hotomani\'s Sanctuary. I\'ll have to go and free him.";
D.q[2204] = "Hem... I don\'t want to be rude, but apart from MacGiven, I don\'t know anybody who could make a bow with this stuff...";
D.q[1378] = "Hemm... I\'m busy at the moment.";
D.q[7764] = "I\'m not for sale. Tell that drunk that if he wants my mugwort, he needs to come here and apologise in person.";
D.q[7100] = "";
D.q[7216] = "";
D.q[1070] = "Hem...Can\'t you see I\'m busy?";
D.q[1103] = "Tell me buddy, have you seen my brothers roaming around here?\nI\'ve to find them as soon as possible. They tend to smash things and throw the pieces at anyone who gets in their way.";
D.q[7765] = "What? He wants me to apologise because I asked him if his invention was a manure recycling machine? Does he think I\'m some kind of idiot?";
D.q[4500] = "Selling over.\nSo then, I\'ve a friend who could take care of it. But he\'s a strange person, and has a tendency to get paranoid. Very paranoid, that is. \nHe\'s hiding out in Brouce Boulgoure\'s cave at the clearing, but I can\'t go visit him as a very unusual beast called Bellus Sel has blocked the entrance. You\'ll notice that all this will sort out Nara\'s business, and you know how Nara hates to be disturbed.";
D.q[6109] = "It\'s my turn to go. I can\'t sit back and let him risk his life like this.";
D.q[1558] = "Moo oom holp m\'om plos\'om moo oom.";
D.q[1361] = "*Paper*\nHey, but how...? It\'s impossible... Cheater!";
D.q[7766] = "I understand your problem, I\'m not stupid. I refuse to go and ridicule myself in front of that idiotic Eniripsa, and nothing and nobody will make me change my mind.";
D.q[6639] = "I took just a few minutes for Elturt to win the fight and send you to your maker.";
D.q[3058] = "Here are the planks. I\'ll use them for the framework. Now, I\'ll need rocks for the walls.";
D.q[5346] = "";
D.q[7101] = "";
D.q[7767] = "And what will I do with all that money, do you think? I can have a cool drink whenever I want to here, and it doesn\'t cost me a thing.";
D.q[1153] = "Before you leave the temple, I\'d like you to do a little test.\nI\'m going to ask you a few questions to make sure You\'re ready to discover the world. If you pass with success, I\'ll teach you a meditative technique which can be quite useful.";
D.q[760] = "For almost a hundred years, we\'ve abandoned the cemetery East of Bonta. Since then, many creatures have infiltrated its walls.\nOne of them is particularly tough: the mummy nova.\nTake it as a test, but if you bring me some pieces of its wrapping, I\'ll name you officer of the militia of Bonta.";
D.q[6046] = "";
D.q[7102] = "";
D.q[1044] = "Here it is! As good as new.";
D.q[4839] = "";
D.q[662] = "Oh! Somebody... Go away! No, come back!... What\'s your name? I\'ve been in for 5 years... You?  \n \nWhy are you staring at me like that? I lost my memory... I remember how it happened very clearly... anyway... Commander Chaferfu my Captain??!! I\'ve a secret, sir, do you want to hear it ?";
D.q[7768] = "Have you seen his face? I\'d rather kiss a Mastogob!";
D.q[4844] = "Here you are again! Did you put the potion on Divad\'s table?";
D.q[7769] = "You don\'t have anything that interests me. I drink all I want here, and I\'m not wanting for ice cubes, either.";
D.q[677] = "Congratulations! You successfully completed the dungeon.\n\nAs a reward, I\'ll give you this pet. It will prove useful in your quest.";
D.q[3859] = "You find gift for Bworknroll. You go with Litol.";
D.q[3855] = "Aah! Feet up while admiring Astrub... this is an old dream. The only thing missing in the picture is a Dofus or two to put on top of the fireplace.";
D.q[5889] = "";
D.q[1244] = "Here you are, freshly ground powder!";
D.q[3875] = "So? What about the crypts?";
D.q[3131] = "Before you start breeding a Dragoturkey, you must capture it, and to do so, you must attract its attention, hypnotize it and then catch it with a net. As you probably know, the only way to hypnotize a Dragoturkey is to cast a spell on it. And I\'m the only one who can teach it to you. I\'ll do my best, but I\'ll bet you\'ll never be as good a Dragoturkey breeder as I\'m.";
D.q[2696] = "Here you go! Give him this magnificent counterfeit Dofus on behalf of the Enutrofs of Astrub. We are all stuck in quarantine.";
D.q[5087] = "";
D.q[7770] = "Is this a joke?\nHmmm, when are you free?";
D.q[1669] = "Here you go! You\'re not very lucky, but maybe you\'ll get a bigger prize with the next Quaquack.";
D.q[2457] = "Here\'s a shadow that\'ll stay in the shade for a good while.";
D.q[7771] = "That\'s good, me too. Go to the tavern at this time, and don\'t let me down.";
D.q[335] = "There you go, now you know the basics of the profession. One last thing before you go, you need the right tool for the job. Have a look at the ones I\'m selling.";
D.q[484] = "Here, I\'ve written down on this parchment the list of missions yet to be accomplished. Don\'t hesitate to ask me for further information.";
D.q[3017] = "Strange phenomena are disturbing the tranquillity of those who\'re supposed to rest here. I\'m trying to understand what\'s going on.... If you\'re not scared of ghosts and not afraid to lose your mind, come help me!";
D.q[7772] = "I thought you\'d come. Take a chair and sit down.\nDo you want something to eat? Don\'t look that that, this one\'s on me.";
D.q[3603] = "Here. Now you know everything you need to know to start. Go and see the boss. He\'ll give you work to do.";
D.q[2512] = "Here, give him this magnificent counterfeit Dofus on behalf of the Enutrofs of Astrub. ";
D.q[7783] = "My friends and I tried hard to get rid of the ticks by shearing the infected calves. Alas, most of them succumbed to the Lurgi in the weeks that followed.\nWe\'ve resumed contact with the mainland at the right time because we can seek professional help. Will you help us?";
D.q[3881] = "Why does he want my services? Can\'t he hire someone else?";
D.q[3474] = "Hey hey you! Come, come!";
D.q[7773] = "Don\'t be shy.\nSo what are you talking about? Wait, let\'s get that dry throat seen to first.\nInnkeeper, two large gins, two pints of cider. Ice in the cider.";
D.q[4671] = "Very kind you are, and delicious this salad is. Brought me a Spentox Back-Scratcher you have? Mmmmm, I should accept it not. Been able to scratch my back for years I have not. So, strike a deal with you I will. For the back-scratcher the location of the Fogornleg Horn reveal I will.\nFind the horn to the north-east of the island, you will, near a phoenix statue.\nNow to bed I must go, very sleepy the salad made me...";
D.q[4123] = "Hey doryphore! It\'s me! Captain Haddock\'n\'roll! I can take you to the other end of the world, especially if it takes you away from me! \nIf you\'re interested, I can take you to a wonderful desert island where there aren\'t any Kanniballs, or any balls at all, for that matter.";
D.q[5887] = "";
D.q[1318] = "It\'s just wonderful! I\'m a rich man ha-ha-ha! Clear off now!";
D.q[7774] = "You see, do you have things to tell. Go on, have another little drink to warm you up some more.";
D.q[5935] = "Hey there little Gobtubby! I\'m here for you to trade any sweets you have which are no longer edible. Don\'t ask me why I\'m trading you delicious sweets against others that are not edible, it\'s a cock-and-bull story! And trust me you don\'t want to be facing that bull... ";
D.q[3646] = "Hey there! I\'m glad to see a new face! Let me introduce myself... my name is Tellih\'Gent. Aha, that\'s not a very popular name around here, I can tell you, though I met a Sadida with the same name once. We didn\'t talk for very long, but I could tell he was a nice person. He fell asleep after a while, so I left. Imagine that, fell asleep. Must have been sick! Ho! That reminds me of a funny story that happened a long time ago while I was napping myself. Do you want to hear it?";
D.q[7785] = "What? I had forgotten that time continues to flow in places other than the island. Well, in that case, go and see his replacement.";
D.q[5353] = "";
D.q[3162] = "Hey #1, do you know who I am? You must\'ve heard of me - I\'m Krunchie, the greatest Crackler hunter of all time! I catch them, I twist them, I beat them, I disassemble them, I dismember them, I break them, they go \"crack\", they go \"boom\", they go... as you can see, I truly am the greatest Crackler hunter.";
D.q[7775] = "I\'ve got one of those headaches... Pass me the bottle, will you, it\'s the best way to deal with a hangover.\nDon\'t pull that face, you\'ve convinced me to go and see Jon Burrowman so that he\'ll forgive me.\nYou happy now?";
D.q[7786] = "I fear that this problem is beyond my area of expertise. I do not know of any miracle cure that will get rid of ticks and treat infected Mastogobs, however, an old friend may be able to help you. His name is Wogew the Hewmit, I\'ll tell you where he lives.";
D.q[4145] = "Did you bring me everything I need to properly breed my creatures?";
D.q[7776] = "I\'ve got one of those headaches... Pass me the bottle, will you, it\'s the best way to deal with a hangover.\nDon\'t pull that face, you\'ve convinced me to go and see Jon Burrowman so that he\'ll forgive me.\nYou happy now?";
D.q[4277] = "Hey there... hehehe... Watch out, this forest is anything but quiet.";
D.q[2002] = "Hey you! Dad wants to talk to you...he\'s over there, south of here, by the lake... Wait, I\'ll show you on your map.";
D.q[3816] = "Hey! Don\'t give up so easily... You won\'t get far with that attitude. Have another go sometime!";
D.q[7787] = "I see, I have an idea but I need live specimens of ticks and some blood samples. Bwing me a dozen ticks and a blood sample fwom each type of Mastogob so that I can study them.";
D.q[1151] = "You\'re in a Bow Kennel. This building is home to all small pets. We keep them when their master has to go slay dragons. We pamper them and we make sure they\'re well treated. We can even take a pet ghost and in exchange, give you a new pet.";
D.q[7777] = "I don\'t know how you managed it, but Cap\'n Tankerous came to apologise. I was so stunned that I forgot to give him the mugwort, and he left, forgetting to take it.\nHere, take him this. I am a man of my word, not like that damned Count Harebourg.";
D.q[5818] = "";
D.q[2069] = "Hey, I need a shovel. Woohoo! A shovel... I\'m saved! Dig... I\'m going deeper underground... Underground is safe...";
D.q[3458] = "Hey! You, ahaha no! Not the pink Minotoror! Yes you! Ahahaha!";
D.q[3245] = "S..S...So, you see a rune it\'s somethin\' extremely mystical and ultra powerful, but I d...d...don\'t have much info ab..bout it. All I know is th....th....that as s....s...soon as you use it, it\'s as if you w...w...were posted on the World\'s aura... you s...s...see, somethin\' like that. And any one c...c...can s...s...see you\'re a craftsman! And there you go! You\'re known, and renowned and K-K-Kamas are yours!";
D.q[7778] = "Oh, I forgot that one.\nI\'ll get you a bucket of water. Hurry up and take it to the doctor before it freezes, it not even good enough to make ice cubes to cool drinks.";
D.q[1129] = "We can be diabolical and trendy at the same time, can\'t we?";
D.q[238] = "Whaaa! But what...? Who...? But...? Wawa, it looks like you\'re lost... Buzz off! I\'ve got to get past! Can\'t you see I\'m trying to work here!";
D.q[7779] = "You too your time... Mind you, it helped me make good progress in my research. I\'ll need to ask you one last service, but it could be dangerous.\nI have just given an experimental vaccine to a guinea pig that I keep in the cellar, but it won\'t let me near it. I need a blood sample from it to examine the effect of the vaccine. Can you sort that out for me?\nHe broke the opening mechanism so you will need help to get in.";
D.q[7790] = "Thank you fow coming. I twuly believe that wowking with one of the gweat alchemists, we\'ll obtain some stupendous wesults.\nHuwwy up and let youw fwiend know it\'s only a mattew of time befowe we have a solution to his tick pwoblem.";
D.q[3660] = "Hey, I recognise you! You\'ve worked for me before, haven\'t you? Anyway, you couldn\'t have arrived at a better time, I need someone I can trust. Could you take this tool to Xelorat Masket? She\'s quite a long way away and I don\'t have time to go myself at the moment.";
D.q[4119] = "And now, here comes the last and most important question: how many Traumatised Kokonuts can a Crow carry if it has 5 times less strength than you, but which has a Bherb Belt and a bag made of Pikoko hair improved by a costumagus?";
D.q[7835] = "Do you want to descend into the Pingwin\'s Lair?";
D.q[1698] = "Alright, alright... Just take an object from this big bag. Some of them are worth a real fortune! Trust me!";
D.q[3288] = "What was I saying...\nRight, I was stuck on this island and Otomai often failed his brain trepanations and transplantations on monsters. \nFor example, did you know that a Iop brain can fit in an Arachnee head?\nAnyway, to help him in his noble task, his knowledge quest, I built a time-travelling machine that helped him try again some of his experiences.";
D.q[1038] = "Hey, Musa the Wolf Shooter told you it was easy but it\'s not THAT easy! Handling a hunter\'s weapon requires a few skills. Let Musa have proof of your dexterity and he will name you hunter.";
D.q[4816] = "";
D.q[7781] = "I need a sample of Mastogob Blood to create new doses of vaccine.";
D.q[7791] = "You say they will help me? The last time someone promised to help us, an eternal winter hit Frigost. Fields once filled with grain and farmers are now abandoned, and my poor calves have almost nothing to put in their mouths. Well, we\'ll see if these hunters keep their promise.";
D.q[7146] = "";
D.q[8111] = "";
D.q[3806] = "Hey, hey... take it easy... No way am I giving you this magic necklace for that tired old moth-eaten piece of skin.";
D.q[4867] = "Totally. That tavern keeper might be good at collecting bribes, but his cooking is another story. Why are two guards like us eating the same food as the prisoners, that\'s what I want to know!?";
D.q[5187] = "Why accuse me? You had all the proof you needed of my innocence. What have I done to you?";
D.q[8112] = "";
D.q[1159] = "Congratulations! You deserve to learn my meditation technique.\nInjuries inflicted by the creatures of this world are usually superficial.\nTo heal through meditation, you must sit and let the eniripisan magic of this world overcome your body.\n\nNow go! The world awaits you!";
D.q[8113] = "";
D.q[3947] = "Ah, marvellous! Here are the ingredients. Give me a moment, I stir like this, I lower the heat and now you\'re a Wabbit!";
D.q[7747] = "Although durable, Frosteez are difficult to maintain and reproduce, and we are still far from having sufficient quantities such that the entire population has enough to eat. Unfortunately, our dwindling reserves of seeds and growing capacity of our greenhouses is limited. It would be very kind of you to help renew our supply of seeds. What do you say?\nIf you agree, I need 50 Pea Seeds that you\'ll find stuck to the hair of Mastogobs, a dozen Emmer Seeds that sometimes grow in fields and some Frosteez Seeds.";
D.q[5360] = "";
D.q[8114] = "";
D.q[1016] = "Hey, you don\'t have half enough here. Amayiro did tell me you weren\'t exactly the crunchiest peanut in the bag. As usual, he was dead right...";
D.q[5175] = "";
D.q[8115] = "";
D.q[7215] = "";
D.q[4450] = "Ahh, but you\'re a Brakmarian! What do you want from me?";
D.q[1265] = "Hum, thanks. I\'ll bring that to Ture Inge for a complete analysis.";
D.q[8116] = "";
D.q[3139] = "What is such a despicable being doing in Master Skeunk\'s hideout?  \nYou don\'t intend to go through this door, do you?  \nOnly adventurers who have permission from the disciples of Skeunk - the four sisters - are allowed to go through this door.";
D.q[8117] = "";
D.q[1573] = "Hi there #1, you lookin for a good time?";
D.q[5903] = "";
D.q[1194] = "Hi Brakmarian Comrade, how can I help you?";
D.q[646] = "What a misfortune! What Betrayal! What has happened to my Brave Gobballs, yesterday so nice, so helpful, so protective...and now so nasty and stupid! \n\nThey have completely changed in a matter of a few days. Their name never suited them so well as it does now!\nThey attack everything that moves and gobble it all up... My Royal Gobball swallowed 4 Eniripsas, 2 Ecaflips and a Iop in the last few hours! I\'m distraught. They don\'t listen to me anymore! The only solution is to take the Gobball by the horns and let them have it!\nHelp me calm them down! Please....\nI\'ll make it worth your while.";
D.q[4285] = "I\'m telling you the truth. I\'d never betray Bonta. I\'m far from perfect, but I\'m faithful to the principles that our city is founded on. I swear to you on Jiva\'s head... I beg of you, don\'t turn me in... I\'ll never buy food from the Brakmarians again! I\'ve other suppliers. They\'re expensive, but I\'ll buy from them, ok.";
D.q[7219] = "";
D.q[1368] = "The garrison must protect the villagers when they\'re attacked by Eastern warriors.";
D.q[1367] = "Hi, my name is Hertuen. I\'m here to defend the door of the Amakna garrison. How can I help you?";
D.q[2041] = "Hi there! Let me introduce myself, I\'m Dragonsly, the alchemist of this good old city. What can I do for you?";
D.q[7792] = "I\'m really starting to worry. My boss, Valy Domidat set off to repair the plumbing system that heats the Farmer\'s Workshop in the Icefields. In the worst case, if the problem is really important, she\'ll return before dark and we prepare all the necessary work together, but she\'s been absent for several days and nobody has seen her.\nCan you try to find her, please? Everyone needs her here.";
D.q[1377] = "Strange, very strange. A very powerful magic flux causes disruptions in the magmatic current. And even stranger... a little further on I discovered the door of what I believe to be a fortress. It seems that some kind of mechanism opens it. With some more time, I\'ll be able to solve the mystery.";
D.q[4793] = "Good work. Now we must verify Nope\'s statement. If someone followed Kit Dingaround, I want to know who it was.\nRetrace the exact route Kit Dingaround took on the day of his arrest. Go from the Farmers\' Market to the Smiths\' Workshop, then to the Shoemakers\' Workshop and finally to Atyu Sirvis\' Inn. Ask all the passersby that you meet along the way if any of them saw anything that day. Once you have additional information or clues, talk to Ture Inge, we need his expert advice.\nGo now, I trust you. May Silvosse guide you to the truth.";
D.q[2083] = "Hi there! Wanna play with me? You\'re the prey and I\'m the huntress? *She takes out an arrow and aims her bow at you*";
D.q[7793] = "So, did you find Valy? Tell me she\'s well.";
D.q[306] = "Hi there, I see you know the anthem of Chip Endale, Rescue Ranger. When you need some help to save the day, I\'m never far away. I draw strength from Nutelli and to make Nutelli, I need hazelnuts and lots of love. I\'m interested in both. I can give you a Chafer Archer Thighbone in exchange for 5 hazelnuts.";
D.q[389] = "Hi! I love the Nutelli that Chip Endale makes but my father says it\'s too expensive... So I tried to make some myself... If you mix 70 acorns with 70 Evil Dandelion Tongues, you get a mixture close to Mr Endale\'s concoction. Bring me the ingredients and I\'ll give you an Agility scroll.";
D.q[1334] = "Hi! I\'m Captain Koda. I\'m very busy preparing an important Brakmarian attack with nine of my men.";
D.q[7794] = "Valy is busy at the moment, come back later, and in the meantime, take the opportunity to visit our town.";
D.q[945] = "Hi! I\'m Kosuke the Blade Smith. How can I help you ?";
D.q[4358] = "Ecaflips, huh... yes, I had a few of them over not so long ago. They looked dodgy too, by the way. I think I overheard them talking about someone by the name of Lodax, not that I was listening or anything.";
D.q[5591] = "What have you done to me? I\'m tingling all over... and the pain... You dirty little mongrel, I\'m sure it\'s because of your urine. By the way, you really should stop drinking, your breath smells foul.";
D.q[8076] = "";
D.q[6256] = "What up with Captain Starky anyway? That wimp doesn\'t even reach up to my ankle, I\'ll crush him and his Cheekens, I\'ll stamp on them, I\'ll climb on a chair and jump on them until all that\'s left is bony mud. Then I\'ll drink the Bontarian Cheeken juice for breakfast, the next day I mean.";
D.q[7795] = "The Farmer\'s Workshop is in the fields east of the village. There was a problem with the pipe that feeds the north. Start your search there.";
D.q[7220] = "";
D.q[3546] = "Hi! Sorry, I didn\'t mean to hurt you... ah ah ah sorry for the bad joke. I know that Sacriers, usually demand an eye for an eye, if not two. That\'s a good thing. I don\'t need cheek turners... I need cheek... eh... tearers. I can see in your eyes you\'re game!";
D.q[8077] = "";
D.q[7796] = "Strangely, the snowman\'s eyes follow your movements.\nYou don\'t notice anything else in the area, Francky will be disappointed.";
D.q[8078] = "";
D.q[1430] = "You\'re at the schwimming pool. My creation.";
D.q[5885] = "";
D.q[5618] = "What does this little Militiawoman want with us? Go do this, go do that, wait here, meet me there. They say jump and she asks how high?. Pathetic.";
D.q[121] = "Hi, I\'m Hugo Bello, young Feca Master. I love tickling my Gobballs to make them squeal.";
D.q[7797] = "Thanks to you, Valy is safe, and I\'ll be in employment a little while longer yet.";
D.q[8079] = "";
D.q[1433] = "Blast, you really landed yourself in it! The best thing for you to do is to make fake proofs and find a culprit because Amayiro won\'t easily give up.\nBesides you shouldn\'t trust him, I can sense that he\'s jealous of you...";
D.q[4426] = "Any news of Kaffra?";
D.q[1362] = "*Stone*\nHey, but how? It\'s not possible... Cheater!";
D.q[7798] = "I don\'t understand, she\'s far too clever to have been tricked by those pesky Mastogobs.\nEveryone here likes her, she redecorated plenty of houses after the freeze, I don\'t know who could have it in for her.\nYou really didn\'t notice anything unusual?";
D.q[5228] = "";
D.q[8080] = "";
D.q[102] = "Hi, I\'m Laura Soho, I\'ll be your waitress today. What can I get for you?";
D.q[7123] = "";
D.q[7103] = "";
D.q[946] = "Hi, I\'m Allen Tokar, do ya wanna a beer?\nTell me, would you have 4 Kamas to lend me? I\'ll pay you back as soon as I get my wages... Actually, would you have 8?";
D.q[8081] = "";
D.q[373] = "Hi, I\'m Ariz. I make gum-based sweets. To make gum, I need lots of jelly...";
D.q[7799] = "What has that got to do with Valy\'s disappearance?\nNow that I think about it, there was a stranger who went to her workshop the other night, just before closing. I heard talk her talking to Valy and they had a fight. It was the first time in a century I\'d heard Valy arguing with someone. Valy then returned and told me she would repair the pipes at the Farmer\'s Workshop at dawn. She was very upset and most importantly, the temperature had dropped several degrees at once, as if winter had arrived in the building for the second time.\nI even had to ask Jean-Pierre Kofkof to come and warm the building since the cold seemed to have settled there for good.";
D.q[8082] = "";
D.q[7725] = "It\'s brass monkeys out there. It\'s been almost a century now and I still haven\'t managed to get used to it. If they\'d listed to my idea instead of the Count of Strasbourg\'s, we wouldn\'t be in this mess. When the crops burn, at least it\'s warm.\nI\'m seriously thinking  of settling in the north of the island, near the Lava Tunnels. The only thing that bothers me if I go there, is that it\'s near the castle of the Clumsy Count.";
D.q[100] = "Hi, I\'m Rish Claymore, a respected Master-at-arms in Amakna. If you\'re looking for a Whetstone you\'re in luck, I\'ve one for sale.";
D.q[8083] = "";
D.q[1254] = "What sort of cloaks? Bontarian cloaks of course. The ones used for every official ceremony in the city.\nAny good tailor can make a cloak with a magic blue dye, a crow\'s feather and white Gobball wool.";
D.q[7800] = "Oh, it wasn\'t much, but I wonder how they made it colder on the inside than on the outside, in spite of the heating.\nIf you need a demonstration, I\'m your man!";
D.q[295] = "Hi, my name is Jackall Breath. I\'m Kwaker Vans\' apprentice, and Edrige Valling\'s fiancé. The problem is she\'s been sick of my breath ever since I started eating this Curryless Curry Bread. Whenever I want to talk to her, I have to eat Mint Jelly, but it\'s getting more and more difficult to find. Will you help me?";
D.q[1240] = "Hi, how can I help?";
D.q[275] = "What could you possibly know about the powers of mushrooms? You\'re not even an Eniripsa...";
D.q[4336] = "What are we going to do with it? Sell it of course. You thought that we were really going to abide by this contract? When Xephires has completed his mission, we\'ll get rid of him... and that\'s that.\nSpeaking of which, I\'ll have to get rid of Milone too... he was really annoying this past while, and he knows too much anyway. But that can wait.";
D.q[8084] = "";
D.q[3133] = "What do you want from me, you cheeky scoundrel.\nI see... You\'re here to give me the Koolich set!\nNo!\nWhat are you talking about?\nYou cheeky...!";
D.q[918] = "Hi, my name is Ture Inge, the famed specialist in spying and psychology. I know you want something from me.";
D.q[7801] = "I have two or three issues to sort out first. Go ahead, I\'ll meet you at the foot of the turbine.";
D.q[3983] = "What do you want from me? Can\'t you see I\'m... questing? I must defeat a cweature wowthy of my lineage. Accowding to this fellow I met who was all dwessed in black, a Tofu hides in the land and I must defeat it if I want to sit on the thwone one day.";
D.q[7124] = "";
D.q[7104] = "";
D.q[8085] = "";
D.q[4474] = "Did you find the Smith?";
D.q[1298] = "Hi, noble fellow citizen, I\'m the steward of the city. May I help you?";
D.q[7802] = "What do you want me to do?\nDo not ask me for my opinion, or I\'ll burn everything.";
D.q[1578] = "Hihi! I hope he will remember the lesson!";
D.q[376] = "Hi, my name is Téha Chicks. I\'m one of the worshippers of the Great Guru. I was once a lost sheep, He showed me the way. Since then, I believe in him, especially just after eating a mushroom doughnut... Skippy gave me the recipe.";
D.q[6544] = "You know how to play and you\'ve an appetite for risk, you don\'t live in Brakmar for nothing.";
D.q[1380] = "Hillik! Iik ik ink skiril. Hiwik cinik iik hilp yik?";
D.q[4842] = "";
D.q[8086] = "";
D.q[2256] = "What? A Gobball? We don\'t have time! We\'ve got to go down...I think they\'ve felt something that\'s not gas... Some came back in a poor state, and I doubt a Subosycold can do something about it. Ours have gone to look for the sniffallrats for a while now... Find them, please!";
D.q[7803] = "Get out of the way, it\'s going to get a little hot.";
D.q[4737] = "Arg! Curses on you, Brakmarian!";
D.q[1973] = "What? That\'s daylight robbery! Fine then, I\'ll mix their beer with water. Deal!";
D.q[4735] = "Hello, my name is Kosuke the... ehh, but you\'re a bloody Brakmarian, what are you doing here!?";
D.q[3242] = "These disciples used to be the inhabitants of this village. They wanted to excessively reproduce the Dreggons of the god Osamodas which they managed to tame. But they were quite ill-intentioned. Indeed, everyone knows that Dofus originate from Dragons. So, for many generations, they kept on reproducing Dragons restlessly in order to get more and more Dofus. They should also have kept in mind that these eggs were cursed and that Dragons cannot be tamed like other creatures...";
D.q[8087] = "";
D.q[6281] = "What? You gave the burglars a thumping and then you managed to convince them in their hideout to come and join the militia? Excellent Brakmarian reflexes! Never forget that the more deceitful people are, the more likely they are to be useful to us eventually.";
D.q[4027] = "The formula is not complete? But I\'ve already told you everything I know...";
D.q[4470] = "What? It\'s strange that you\'d ask me that. A Bontarian passed by here not long ago to ask if he could work for me...\nNo, I don\'t work for Bonta, but I\'ve a friend who has begun doing just that.";
D.q[7804] = "Thank you, you saved me from that terrible spell.";
D.q[1836] = "Hmmmm. Nope, it looks like you\'re still missing something.";
D.q[8088] = "";
D.q[7805] = "It\'s was the stranger. She came and asked me if I would redecorate the Count Harebourg\'s castle, but I refused. When I came here to repair the pipes, I noticed that she was following me. As I looked back, I felt the cold chilling me and I found myself changed into a snowman.\nWho knows what would have happened if you hadn\'t found me. Take these few coins in addition to my gratitude.";
D.q[4449] = "Hello, please don\'t disturb me, I\'m busy with my books.";
D.q[2527] = "Hey there! I\'ve got all sorts of fermented drinks. What can I get you?";
D.q[1304] = "Come back again at 9 p.m. with all the elements inscribed on this list... I\'ll give you all the details of your mission.";
D.q[8089] = "";
D.q[1739] = "Disciple, you still have many things to learn, what do you want to know ?";
D.q[923] = "Hi dead loss! What do ya want ?";
D.q[7806] = "Hello, welcome to my handyman workshop. This place is open to everyone, so make yourself at home.";
D.q[4992] = "";
D.q[1715] = "Congratulations! You\'ll have to be fast to catch this animal, you seem to be talented. If you want to become an even better fighter, I\'ve some advice for you.";
D.q[7125] = "";
D.q[6133] = "So what about those souls I asked you for?";
D.q[4657] = "These documents are very important to Brakmar. \nAny error on your part will be severely punished.";
D.q[8091] = "";
D.q[2831] = "Greetings. The entry of the tower is reserved to the most faithful inhabitants of Bonta, the members of the Orders. If you want to join us, go see Amayiro in the militia barracks.";
D.q[4990] = "Hmm, an attack meant to stop Brakmar controlling the Imp Village? It\'s true that our enemy has been getting more and more aggressive lately. Let\'s cut their supply line... see how rough they are then. \nTell the steward I approve of his plan.";
D.q[1095] = "Hmm, I see you belong to the Bontarian militia.\nAmayiro asked me a report and I\'ve just finished it.\nHere, and may the goddess Jiva bless you #1.";
D.q[8092] = "";
D.q[1347] = "Hmm, if you win a game, I\'ll teach you how to play anywhere with anybody. And win!";
D.q[3103] = "What? Live with him in that shabby little dump with that awful smell of rotten potatoes? Who does he think he\'s...? Bloody con? Find his old hideout instead and come to describe it to me.";
D.q[6545] = "Well, you\'re not backwards in coming forwards, are you? Ecaflips must just love betting with you.";
D.q[1060] = "Hmm, it was an interesting little fight.\nWell, if you\'re finished playing there is still some work for you to do for the clan.";
D.q[8093] = "";
D.q[204] = "Hmm, sorry, but Wiss Catz told me that he never bets unless he\'s totally sure he\'ll win. He\'s not going to take you up on your offer... Here\'s your clover.";
D.q[8090] = "";
D.q[5230] = "";
D.q[4043] = "Thanks! Is that all?";
D.q[280] = "Hmmm ... Yeeeesss! I knew it! Haaa! Such genius! Such intelligence! I\'ve developed a plan that even I\'d call amazing. But for now I need to rally enough people to my cause, I think forty thieves should do the trick ...";
D.q[2403] = "Hmm, the smell of tanned leather really gets my motor runn... oh sorry! I don\'t mean to disturb you, my name is Ygat, I\'m the best shoemaker in the region. Belts, shoes, name it, I can do it!";
D.q[1065] = "Hmmm, leave me alone, can\'t you see I\'m having my break?";
D.q[8094] = "";
D.q[1870] = "Ah Ah! A young girl. Perhaps she\'s a thief or worse... a magician who\'s jealous of my powers! Everything is clear now! Humm, let\'s not rush. Let\'s write this down as a mere assumption.";
D.q[7221] = "";
D.q[8095] = "";
D.q[1486] = "Hmmm. I can\'t teach you the basis of the trade. You\'re already in training for another trade. Come back and see me when you\'ve mastered your other trades.";
D.q[820] = "I\'m quite satisfied with your work, what else do you want?";
D.q[4093] = "Alright, I finished the potion... Ready to become a Wabbit?";
D.q[6542] = "Hmmmfff... Mmmmmffff!";
D.q[1028] = "Hmmm...well....In fact it isn\'t... I can\'t handle my sabre anymore when I wear them. Never mind I\'ll sell them to the jeweller.";
D.q[8096] = "";
D.q[6131] = "So what about those souls I asked you for?";
D.q[1887] = "Well, let\'s deal with this together. Could you go and buy two roses for me? I\'ll show you where to go... give me your map. Okay, there it is. Meanwhile, I\'ll make preparations to leave. First, though, I\'ve to analyse the prints left by the thief.";
D.q[6269] = "Hmm... now that I think about it, it must be possible without dying. Your mission remains the same, but there\'s no need to go paddling through the Brakmar moat and killing yourself. You\'re much more useful to me alive.";
D.q[8097] = "";
D.q[7222] = "";
D.q[2639] = "What? You want me to... Oh! A challenge!\nAlright! I\'m going to squash you and give your leftovers to your Chief Pandawette once I\'ve drowned her in her own spring! Let\'s meet in the dojo!";
D.q[1929] = "Take this ring. I\'d suggest you to fight the Treechnid that hangs about in the forest. The magic waves that spread when it dies are likely to be powerful enough to activate the ring. Good luck! Beware, the Treechnid can be very dangerous. You can ask for help/ The ring is yours anyway.";
D.q[8098] = "";
D.q[4777] = "There was something fishy about that guy. I was him chatting with another suspicious type. They were talking business over a drink.\nThen they set up a meeting so that he could give him the stolen documents.";
D.q[7126] = "";
D.q[1935] = "Thanks for the report... I\'m surrounded by a bunch of idiots. Let\'s see... what in the name of Sram is he talking about? I can\'t even read it...\'excavation team\'...\'another discovery\'...damn! I want to know what this is all about!";
D.q[467] = "Blimey, you\'we a big one! Don\'t mess with me, mate, I\'m the Peawly Mowning Wabbit, one of the most powewful Wabbits in the wowld. I\'ve been blessed by the Singing Staw, so stop looking at me like that, ow thewe\'ll be twouble! You wouldn\'t attack me, would you? I caused the destwuction of the gweat Effete Towew, you know... \n \nStop stawing at me! You wouldn\'t attack me, wight? Look at me! I\'m tiny, I\'m all alone, and I have such sweet little eyes. You couldn\'t huwt such a lovely cweatuwe, could you? You know what they say, the stwongest shouldn\'t attack the weakest...wight? Wight? I tell you what, how about I give you a nice, shiny key and you leave me alone. Deal?";
D.q[8099] = "";
D.q[1218] = "Thanks and welcome, Bro!";
D.q[8100] = "";
D.q[2682] = "Hola! Do you like this sweet fermented bamboo perfume?! We\'ll get on well then... What do you want?";
D.q[5693] = "I felt an evil aura, and I thought of you right away.\nWhat do you want?";
D.q[1938] = "What?! Me? Give up my business?... must be yankin\' my crank! You told him, right?! Not a chance! That\'d finish me off. Well, hurry up and tell my men we\'re sending \'em more hands! Oh... and take this shovel, I\'m sure it\'ll come in handy! So would some luck! Only a Sram can survive a stiff shovel up the...";
D.q[4058] = "Hello, I\'m Otomai, one of the most renowned magicians in the World of Twelve, the uncontested expert on everything that animates and controls living things. I\'m also reputed for my alchemy which I use to brew potions with many different effects. What would you like to know?";
D.q[1220] = "Thanks and welcome, Bro!";
D.q[5048] = "";
D.q[4164] = "We were supposed to find a new world, live a new life and fall in love all over again. \nOur euphoria was as intense as it was brief. Look at me now... I had to run away to make my husband react... even if I know that I\'m going to hurt him by behaving like this. Please explain this to him. He can be as innocent as a Kaniger and as stubborn as a Pikoko sometimes. But his defects are also part of him and I love him just as he\'s. Please, talk to him, and with a bit of luck he\'ll understand and we\'ll be able to start all over again.";
D.q[8101] = "";
D.q[1202] = "You can now join the Order of the Salvatory Spirit.\nAre you still sure of your choice ?";
D.q[3172] = "Hoo Hoo Krabill madok! Huhuharg. Kirball wowo?";
D.q[1582] = "Honesty doesn\'t run in the family, so don\'t think that a respectable person is hidden inside every nasty Bontarian you come across.";
D.q[3953] = "Horrible marriage? But Allisteria is so... Hey! Wait a minute! You don\'t speak like a Wabbit! You\'re not the prince! Help me, my faithful Gobball!";
D.q[8102] = "";
D.q[3998] = "honour is gained in battle, not in slavery!";
D.q[724] = "We\'ve a double agent in the ranks of the Brakmar Militia, his name is Bishom Pot. Infiltrate the militia and ask him to tell you the orders I gave him. \nTo get in touch with him, just say: Brakmar is a putrid city at this time of year.";
D.q[2169] = "How come you\'re back so fast? You\'re not afraid of Arachnees are you?";
D.q[4905] = "Greetings, you did that quickly.\nI sent spies to find the Spirit of Light, but they returned empty-handed. I\'ve already explained the situation to Elviana Tirips and he will find out more about it. Go see where he is in his research and ask if you can be of any help.";
D.q[2234] = "How d\' you expect to get a good bow if you don\'t bring wool for the string?";
D.q[8103] = "";
D.q[1997] = "Dizbi flower you said? Yeah! I\'m your man! I\'ve exactly what you need! I know the Eniripsa very well. If you prefer it in tea, Dragonsly should be able to make some up. By the way, it would be great if you could bring some back...";
